      "full_body_preview": "The librarian kept two shelves.\n\nThe left shelf held books people had asked for: histories of weather, monographs on bee migration, the third revised edition of \"On the Etiquette of Doors.\" Each volume had been requested by name, signed for, sometimes wept over before it was opened. The shelf was full and warm and smelled faintly of someone's grandmother.\n\nThe right shelf held books pulled at random from the central stacks. A treatise on bridge tariffs. A pamphlet about the moral status of fog. "
    }
